<div class="js-tweet-text-container">
  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="4">This is right. We need a serious proactive programme of political education and training about antisemitism within <a href="/UKLabour" class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="14291684"><s>@</s><b>UKLabour</b></a> but we should also recognise the seriousness of the determination to stamp it out by <a href="/jeremycorbyn" class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="117777690"><s>@</s><b>JeremyCorbyn</b></a><a href="https://t.co/BL9qAsXHWK" rel="nofollow noopener" dir="ltr" data-expanded-url="https://twitter.com/mehdirhasan/status/978384794311643136" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" target="_blank" title="https://twitter.com/mehdirhasan/status/978384794311643136"><span class="tco-ellipsis"></span><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="js-display-url">twitter.com/mehdirhasan/st</span><span class="invisible">atus/978384794311643136</span><span class="tco-ellipsis"><span class="invisible"></span></span></a></p>

  <div class="QuoteTweet-container">

          <div class="QuoteTweet-text tweet-text u-dir" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="2" dir="ltr">You can agree that anti-Semitism is definitely a problem on some parts of the left and needs to be loudly denounced while also agreeing that Jeremy Corbyns political opponents are cynically using it as a stick with which to beat him. You can walk and chew gum at the same time.</div>

  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="0">Freezing cold weather here in Watford. <div class="js-tweet-text-container">
  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="4">Could this be the same Tory Education Secretary Damian Hinds who yesterday said "the mere repetition of a falsehood doesn't make it turn into the truth" while trying to justify axing school meals? <img class="Emoji Emoji--forText" src="https://abs.twimg.com/emoji/v2/72x72/1f914.png" draggable="false" alt="" title="Thinking face" aria-label="Emoji: Thinking face" /><a href="/hashtag/FreeSchoolMeals?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>FreeSchoolMeals</b></a><a href="https://t.co/7WM36Wjd8C" rel="nofollow noopener" dir="ltr" data-expanded-url="https://twitter.com/tes/status/973871815067144193" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" target="_blank" title="https://twitter.com/tes/status/973871815067144193"><span class="tco-ellipsis"></span><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="js-display-url">twitter.com/tes/status/973</span><span class="invisible">871815067144193</span><span class="tco-ellipsis"><span class="invisible"></span></span></a></p>
</div>


<p class="u-hiddenVisually" aria-hidden="true" data-aria-label-part="3">Angela Rayner added,</p>
  
      <div class="QuoteTweet&#10;    &#10;    &#10;    u-block js-tweet-details-fixer">
  <div class="QuoteTweet-container">

  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="0">Its time to act on hate speech.
 
Watch, retweet and help <a href="/hashtag/endthehate?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>endthehate</b></a>.

It stood against landlordism and monopoly. It wanted fair rents, an eight hour day and healthy homes.<a href="https://t.co/5RWeCH1uwV" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" data-pre-embedded="true" dir="ltr">pic.twitter.com/5RWeCH1uwV</a></p>

  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="0">More Tory MPs now support votes for 16yr olds. By my count, Govn now doesnt have a majority to stop it. Choice: lose in Commons, 16yr olds get vote &amp; Tories lose even more support of young people; or back votes at 16 &amp; get some credit for major social reform.  Hmmm. Tough one.</p>

  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="0">The Tories have cut 190 police officers and 59 community support officers in Hertfordshire.

Only Labour will stand up for the safety of our communities. Labour will put 10,000 extra bobbies on the beat.<a href="https://t.co/mo7vnydHk2" rel="nofollow noopener" dir="ltr" data-expanded-url="https://action.labour.org.uk/page/content/police-cut-calculator/" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" target="_blank" title="https://action.labour.org.uk/page/content/police-cut-calculator/"><span class="tco-ellipsis"></span><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="js-display-url">action.labour.org.uk/page/content/p</span><span class="invisible">olice-cut-calculator/</span><span class="tco-ellipsis"><span class="invisible"></span></span></a></p>

And with a great party behind him ready to go out leafleting &amp; canvassing to get him elected.
Thoroughly enjoyed being with everyone this evening.<a href="https://t.co/5L5XmjM0l5" rel="nofollow noopener" dir="ltr" data-expanded-url="https://twitter.com/watfordlabour/status/959540767596384260" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" target="_blank" title="https://twitter.com/watfordlabour/status/959540767596384260"><span class="tco-ellipsis"></span><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="js-display-url">twitter.com/watfordlabour/</span><span class="invisible">status/959540767596384260</span><span class="tco-ellipsis"><span class="invisible"></span></span></a></p>

  </button>
  <div class="dropdown-menu is-autoCentered">
  <div class="dropdown-caret">
    <div class="caret-outer"></div>
    <div class="caret-inner"></div>

  <ul>
